O.J.
Simpson, a former sports star, was found liable for the 1994 murders of his ex-wife Nicole Brown-Simpson and her friend Ron Goldman.
Despite being acquitted in a racially charged trial, Simpson was arrested in Las Vegas for an armed robbery involving sports memorabilia.
He faces multiple felony charges and his co-defendants are pleading guilty to reduced charges.
The incident at the Palace Station casino involved guns and led to a series of arrests.
Simpson's tumultuous past, including the infamous murder trial, continues to haunt him as he navigates legal troubles once again.
